From 30d0fb1550cd2bc07458ea2f6a9c3eca0ee9b1de Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: User-3090 <71881005+User-3090@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 08:03:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 4/8] fix: propagate child OSC 12 cursor colors

Track child OSC 12 sets and OSC 112 resets in pane state, preserve them through
cursor settling and virtual rendering, and carry the optional color in semantic
frames. Native cursors receive minimal OSC color changes; software cursors use
the child color as their fill and fall back to the queried host color.

Restore transient child cursor overrides independently from foreground and
background channels, including when a host color channel is still unknown.
The FrameData wire addition uses protocol 18 from patch 0001; no second bump is
needed because that series protocol is already newer than released protocol 17.

